<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Gay" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Gay,</orth> fine, showy: <cit><quote>rich caparisons or trapping g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 286" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 286</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>ere beauty's dead fleece made another g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 68.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 68, 8</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>so costly g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.146.4" default="NO" valid="yes">146, 4</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the learned man hath got the lady g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 225" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 225</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>g. vestments,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 94</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my g. apparel,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.149" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 149</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.2.66" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 66</bibl>. <cit><quote>g. new coats,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.118" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 3, 118</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>g. ornaments,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.149" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 149</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>never lacked gold and yet went never g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 151</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to lay his g. comparisons apart,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 26</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>